WASHINGTON—The media firm that helped propel Vermont Sen. Bernie Sanders’s 2016 insurgent campaign is splitting from the presidential contender at the start of his second White House bid, citing creative disagreements.

Devine Mulvey Longabaugh said Tuesday it was “stepping away” from the senator’s 2020 president campaign “because we believe that Sen. Sanders deserves to have media consultants who share his creative vision for the campaign."

